Jailed former Bosasa C-O-O Angelo Agrizzi has been rushed to hospital. Correctional Services Department Spokesperson Singabakho Nxumalo spoke to Sally Burdett. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Bosasa executive Angelo Agrizzi was moved from the Johannesburg Prison to a hospital on Thursday. On Wednesday, Agrizzi appeared in court on fraud and corruption charges and was denied bail. READ: Vincent Smith's bail extended to December The court ruled that Agrizzi's foreign assets make him a flight risk. He appeared alongside former ANC MP Vincent Smith. READ: Angelo Agrizzi's bail application dismissed Smith's bail has been extended to 3 December.